    executiveSummary: "The global climate crisis has reached a tipping point, with record-breaking heat and ocean bleaching causing irreparable damage to the planet. The crisis has universal relevance, high emotional impact, and consistent scientific and public interest, making it a critical issue that requires immediate attention. The consequences of inaction will be catastrophic, with rising sea levels, more frequent natural disasters, and unpredictable weather patterns.",
